thread.title: Driver leads police on I-5 high-speed pursuit
thread.title_full: Driver leads police on I-5 high-speed pursuit | OregonLive.com

author: Elliot Njus | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Driver leads police on I-5 high-speed pursuit
text:
A motorist led police on a high-speed pursuit Saturday evening starting at the Fremont Bridge and heading north on Interstate 5 into Vancouver.
The pursuit took place just before 10 p.m. Saturday after an officer tried to stop the vehicle for speeding. The vehicle fled, said Portland Police Bureau spokesman Sgt. Greg Stewart.
Speeds reached 80 mph, Stewart said. Officers used spike strips to slow the car before it crossed into Washington.
Portland officers broke off the pursuit, but police in Washington stopped the vehicle.
